# Release Notes: v0.3.0 → HEAD

## Summary

This release brings significant orchestration improvements, expanded skill ecosystem, enhanced observability, and refined user experience. Key highlights include the new `gza advance` command for intelligent batch workflow management, LLM-powered learnings summarization, colorized terminal output with Rich formatting, and major architectural improvements including CLI package refactoring and provider-agnostic design.

## Breaking Changes

- **Removed legacy YAML-based task serialization**: Tasks are now stored exclusively in SQLite
- **Deleted `src/gza/tasks.py`**: Legacy task storage module removed; use CLI or API
- **`gza status` renamed to `gza group`**: Update scripts and workflows accordingly
- **Require `gza improve` for task creation**: Direct improve task creation no longer allowed; use `gza improve` after task completion

## New Features

### Commands
- **`gza advance`**: Intelligently orchestrate batch workflow with `--batch B` option to spawn multiple parallel workers
- **`gza implement`**: Create and run implementation tasks from plans (replaces manual workflow)
- **`gza iterate`**: Renamed from `gza cycle`; automated review/improve cycles with configurable max cycle limits
- **`gza group`**: Renamed from `gza status`; display task status groupings
- **`gza set-status`**: Manually force task status updates
- **`gza mark-completed`**: Mark tasks as completed with cleanup

### Skills
- **`gza-code-review-full`**: Comprehensive pre-release code review with test coverage and duplication analysis
- **`gza-plan-review`**: Interactive quality gate for plan tasks before implementation
- **`gza-task-debug`**: Diagnose task failures with loop detection and baseline comparison
- **`gza-task-draft`**: Guided task creation with clarification and refinement
- **`gza-worktree-create`**: Isolated development environment creation with symlinked .gza access
- **`gza-test-and-fix`**: Verify command execution with automated fix and commit

### New Flags & Options
- `--batch B`: Spawn B parallel workers in `gza advance`
- `--poll N`: Refresh `gza ps` output every N seconds
- `--model`, `--provider`: Set LLM provider for commands (add, review, improve)
- `--resolve`: Auto-resolve conflicts in `gza merge` and `gza rebase`
- `--all`: Apply command to all eligible tasks
- `--background`: Run commands in background
- `--dry-run`: Preview changes without execution
- `--new`: Fill batch slots in `gza advance`
- `--update`: Check for and install skill updates

## Major Improvements

### Observability & User Experience
- **Colorized terminal output**: Rich formatting for `gza next`, `gza show`, `gza history`, and logs with colored status indicators
- **Live step count updates**: Real-time step progress in `gza ps` polling
- **Improved `gza ps` display**: Better task visibility, worker tracking, and filtering
- **Startup failure visibility in `gza ps`**: Default `gza ps` now surfaces `failed(startup)` rows, with earliest diagnostics available in `.gza/workers/*-startup.log`
- **Orchestration logging**: Task lifecycle events logged to log files for debugging
- **Orphaned task detection**: Identify and resurface tasks without active workers

### Learning & Context
- **LLM-powered learnings summarization**: Automatic pattern extraction and summarization from completed tasks with Phase 3 implementation
- **Learnings generation**: Generate insights from task history with `gza learnings update --window N`
- **Auto-regeneration**: Learnings automatically regenerated every 5 completed tasks
- **Learnings in worktrees**: Copy learnings to agent worktrees for enhanced context

### Task Management
- **Dropped task status**: New task status for explicitly dropped/cancelled work
- **Task visibility improvements**: Foreground workers now properly registered and visible in `gza ps`
- **Auto-resume failed tasks**: Failed tasks automatically resumed in `gza advance`
- **Improved slug generation**: Better branch naming for review, implement, and improve tasks
- **Selective staging**: Only stage files changed during provider execution

### Architecture & Code Quality
- **CLI package refactoring**: Split monolithic `cli.py` (8,495 lines) into 7 focused modules with full backward compatibility
- **Provider-agnostic design**: Unified review resolution and execution across providers
- **Provider support**: Added OpenAI Codex provider implementation alongside existing Claude provider
- **Unified log output**: LiveLogPrinter class for consistent formatting across commands
- **Code metrics**: Worktree utilities and computation of estimated tokens/costs
- **Test suite optimization**: Reduced wall time from ~97s to ~24s with pytest-xdist parallelization

### Configuration & Flexibility
- **`verify_command` config field**: Custom test/verification command per project
- **`cleanup_days` configuration**: Control worktree retention (default: 30 days)
- **Keychain support**: Fetch auth tokens from macOS keychain for Docker
- **Model & provider persistence**: Resolved model/provider stored with task metadata

## Bug Fixes

- **Fixed false "No changes made" on resume**: Proper change detection during task resumption
- **Fixed background workers silently failing**: Correct project directory argument passing
- **Fixed merge_status tracking**: Lazy migration for existing tasks; proper branch merge detection
- **Fixed Codex review task thrash in Docker**: Session ID and stdin prompt handling
- **Fixed reviewer verdict parsing**: Support multiple formats (`**Verdict**: X`, `## Verdict` headings)
- **Fixed same-branch resolution**: Walks full lineage chain for correct rebase targets
- **Fixed gza unmerged with deleted branches**: Shows unmerged status even when branch deleted
- **Fixed ps poll visibility**: Completed tasks remain visible; accurate status determination
- **Improved merge-to-main handling**: Early exit check for branches with no commits

## Documentation

- **Expanded README**: Added "Why Gza" section explaining batch workflow benefits
- **Detailed quickstart guide**: Step-by-step instructions with improved examples
- **Skills documentation**: Added "Building Skills" section to AGENTS.md
- **Task vs agent context**: Documented distinction for better prompt engineering
- **Code review isolation**: Documentation of review environment setup
- **Worktree lifecycle**: Clear strategy for cleanup and lineage management

## Technical Details

### Database & Persistence
- **Merge status column**: Track merge state in tasks table with backfill for existing data
- **Log file and branch persistence**: Stored in DB at task startup for observability
- **Hourly backups**: SQLite database automatically backed up hourly
- **Step/substep APIs**: Full storage and retrieval for step tracking

### Provider Architecture
- **Multi-provider support**: Claude and Codex providers with unified interface
- **Provider validation**: Compatibility checking between models and providers
- **Docker image management**: Provider-aware rebuilding and caching
- **Model-specific configuration**: Fallback token estimation for non-claude models

### Worker Management
- **Foreground worker registration**: Direct run() calls now properly registered
- **Worker cleanup**: Signal handlers (SIGINT/SIGTERM) for clean shutdown
- **Zombie worker detection**: Auto-cleanup in `gza ps` command
- **Lineage-aware removal**: Interactive prompts before removing worktrees

## Dependencies & Installation

- **Bundled skills**: gza-test-and-fix and other skills included in package distribution
- **Skill auto-installation**: Bundled skills automatically installed in worktrees
- **Update detection**: `--update` flag for skill installation checks
- **Template-based config**: gza.yaml initialized from template for consistency
